PATRONS had to duck bullets when a gang of five gunmen stormed Quiet Vibes Night Club in Dwarsloop near Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga on Sunday, 10 July. Bystanders said they were boozing when the gang emerged and forced them to lie on the floor as they robbed them. “The gang robbed patrons and the owner at gunpoint. They then fired shots randomly, injuring one boozer in the leg before fleeing the scene,” said a bystander. Police spokesman Colonel Donald Mdluli said the cops have launched a manhunt for the five suspects. “Patrons were attacked and robbed of their belongings allegedly by a group of about five armed suspects. “In addition, several items belonging to the owner of the liquor outlet were stolen, including an undisclosed amount of cash, laptop, and liquor. The total value of the items robbed is estimated at about R23 000. One of the victims, aged 29, was shot in the leg during the robbery. ALSO READ | WATCH: Man drops dead after downing Jagermeister! “The suspects are said to have then fled the scene with the stolen items,” he said. Mdluli said the injured victim was taken to hospital for treatment. “Police are investigating a case of business robbery with an additional charge of attempted murder,” he said. Club management confirmed the incident, but didn’t give details.  Mpumalanga police commissioner Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela strongly condemned the incident and called for the swift arrest of the suspects. Anyone with information that can help apprehend the suspects should call CrimeStop on 08600 10111.